// D1.0 net-expansion: INT_MIN / -1 divergence (unmeasured pre-D1.0).
// Interpreter: the divisor==-1 special case (ops.rs) wraps to the minimum and
// prints -128, exit 0. JIT: no guard — Cranelift's sdiv overflow-traps and the
// process dies with STATUS_INTEGER_OVERFLOW (0xC0000095). Both operands are
// variables so the pair reaches runtime instead of semantic analysis. Fix
// lands in the JIT memory-safety gate (D1.2 guards); remove the
// .jit_known_unsound marker then. Note srem does NOT share this trap — see
// t_intmin_mod_neg1, which agrees and is pinned unmarked.
a: t8 = -128
b: t8 = -1
print(a / b)
